-- Accor Says Hennequin to Become CEO From Jan. 15
-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 2010-11-03T06:15:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/hennequin-will-become-accor-chairman-ceo-in-january-replacing-pelisson.html
Accor SA named McDonald’s Corp.’s
Denis Hennequin to take over as chairman and chief executive
officer of the group from Jan. 15 in an e-mailed statement
today.  Hennequin will take over from Gilles Pelisson, whose
contract has been terminated following “strategic
divergences,” Accor said in the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  